<font color="#FF0000">A  SACRED PLACE</font><br>
<tt>Wed Jul 30 17:13:50 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Welcome to the Inner Circle, a place for proven warriors, Dog Soldiers, who have been to war.  It is a special circle where no man can tell another man what to do or think.  It is governed by mutual respect for the emotional and physical wounds of war and that which is embodied in Wanyaka, tuwena Icun'sni, a pledge of proper deportment, where wrong doers remind themselves... look no one behaves in this manner!  It is not a place of Kiyuska... where one breaks his own customs and rules.  Also, the Inner Circle is a place where ever man is Iyotanyapi, honorable and on'simaya... commands recognition.  Above all it is Waonspekiye... a sacred place for teaching and learning with patience.<br>
All who come here to give and receive honor are Mihunka... relatives by choice, Akicita Was`te... good warriors.  They bond together in one voice, Oyate nimkte wacin yelo... I want the people to live (spiritually.)<br>
Those who come here as combat veterans of any war are given the &quot;White Horse Song,&quot; Ta Sunke Ska Olowan, a committment to one another and those to come.  It is a reminder from ancient grandfathers to us and from us to others.<br><br>
               &quot;TA SUNKE SKA OLOWAN&quot;<br><br>
KOLA,TAKU OTEHICA IMACUWAPI LO HENA KOWOKIPI`SNI WAON YELO!<br><br>
Translation into English embodies these meanings:<br>
     &quot;You are my friend, my good friend.  Nothing can stop me from having high regard for you.  I have no fear of death.  I will never abandon or forsake you.  I will always help you.  I will not leave you lying on the battlefield.  I will be your brother forever, you are my friend.&quot;<br><br>
Everyone will bring Wanagi, his spiritual self, here and every man will be Wanagi Yuha, a spirit owner.  There will be brotherhood and healing here.  Mita wasicun he omakiyake, my familiar voice tells me so!
